# Data Dictionary For Gold Layer
## Overview

The Gold layer is the business-level data representation, structured to support analytical and reporting use cases.
It consists of **dimension tables**, and **fact tables** for specific business metrics


### 1. gold.dim_customers
| column_name  | data_type | description |
| ------------- | ------------- | ------------- |
| customer_key | Int | Surrogate key used to identify each custoimer record and to link tables. |
| customer_id | Int  | unqique identifier tied to each customer |
| customer_number  | NVARCHAR(50)  | Unique number that identifies the customer used for tracking and referencing  |
| first_name  | NVARCHAR(50)  | First name of the customer  e.g. James|
| last_name  | NVARCHAR(50)  | last name of the customer E.g. Martins|
| Country  | NVARCHAR(50) | Country the customer comes from E.g. Austrtalia |
| marital status  | NVARCHAR(50)  | Marital Status pof the customer e.g. Single |
| gender  | NVARCHAR(50)  | Gender of the Customer e.g. Male|
| birthdate  | Date  | Birth date of the customer  e.g. 10-10-2025|
| create_date  | Date | Date customer account was created e.g. 11-11-2024 |


### 2. gold.dim_products
| column_name  | data_type | description |
| ------------- | ------------- | ------------- |
| product_key  | INT  | contains a product_key, distinct, used to link other tables  |
| product_id  | INT | contains a product_id, distinct, used to link other tables  |
| product_number  | NVARCHAR(50) | contains a unique product number  |
| product_name  | NVARCHAR(50) | contains a unique product name  |
| category_id  | NVARCHAR(50) | contains information about the category of the product e.g. CO-RF - Components - Road Frame  |
| category  | NVARCHAR(50) | Category of the product e.g. Components  |
| subcategory  | NVARCHAR(50) | subcatagory e.g. Mountain Bikes  |
| maintenance  | NVARCHAR(50) | Does the product require maintenance  |
| cost  | INT  | Cost pper unit for the company |
| product_line  | NVARCHAR(50)  | which product line is the product? part of e.g. road, mountain. Broader and can apply to many products  |
| start_date  | Date | When was the product first supplied  |

### 3. gold.fact_sales
| column_name  | data_type | description |
| ------------- | ------------- | ------------- |
| order_number | NVARCHAR  | Contains the unique order number e.g. 'SO43697'  |
| product_key  | INT  | contains a product_key, distinct, used to link other tables  |
| customer_key  | INT  | Contains a dsistinct customer key, e.g. '10769' used to identify each indivcidual customer/
| order_date  | DATE  | Contains the date the product was mostr recently ordered by a given customer  |
| shipping_date  | DATE  | Contains the date that the p[roduct was shipped  |
| due_date  | DATE  | Contains the date that a product is due to arrive  |
| sales_amount | INT | Sales = Quantity * Price  |
| quantity  | INT  | Amount sold for the specific order line  |
| price  | INT  | price oif the product at time of sale  |



